definitions: Matter, material, articles, or activities of a specified or indeterminate kind that are being referred to, indicated, or implied.
A person's belongings, equipment, or baggage.
Worthless or foolish ideas, speech, or writing; rubbish.
Things in which one is knowledgeable and experienced; one's area of expertise.
The basic constituents or characteristics of something or someone.
Woollen fabric, especially as distinct from silk, cotton, and linen.
(in sport) spin given to a ball to make it vary its course.
A pitcher's ability to produce spin on a ball or control the speed of delivery of a ball.
